Download all the files to a directory/folder.
Your system must have Node.js installed.
Using the terminal/command line, navigate to this directory.
Run 'npm install' on the command line to install required dependencies as mentioned in packasge.json
To run the localhost on port 3000, run 'node app.js' on the command line.
Open the browser and type 'http://localhost:3000/' to run the app.
